Program - ZLSD_RPT10243_CUST_MASTER_TEXT
Includes: ZLSD_RPT10243_TOP
ZLSD_RPT10243_SEL
ZLSD_RPT10243_F01
The program displays and exports customer master text data. It reads customer texts from SAP (KNA1 / KNVV / STXH / TTXIT / TLINE), displays them in an ALV grid with one output row per text line, and allows the user to download the results or navigate directly to XD02 to view or edit a customer's texts.

Includes
ZLSD_RPT10243_TOP – This include contains global type definitions, data declarations, constants, and class definitions.

Defines output structure ty_output with fields KUNNR, NAME1, TDID, TDTEXT, SPRAS, TDLINE — one row per text line as per FDS requirement.
Declares global output table gt_output used across all includes.
Defines all constants: object/table names, BDC field names and ok-codes for XD02 navigation, file type and naming defaults, ALV container name MAIN_CONTAINER and field names, gap widths for header display, Z text type filter constant Z%, top-of-page event name.
Declares class lcl_main with methods: run, build_fcat, display, handle_hotspot_click, download_data.

ZLSD_RPT10243_SEL – This include contains the selection screen definition, field validations, and F4 help.

Block 1 (Partners): S_KUNNR — Customer Number (optional).
Block 2 (Other Criteria): P_KTOKD — Account Group, S_VKORG — Sales Organization (obligatory, no intervals), P_KUKLA — Customer Classification, P_SORTL — Search Term, P_BRSCH — Industry Sector.
Block 3 (Texts): S_TDID — Text Type (obligatory).
Validates S_VKORG against TVKO, S_KUNNR against KNA1, P_KTOKD against T077D, S_TDID against TTXIT for object KNA1. Wildcard * bypasses Text ID validation.
F4 help for S_TDID fetches only Z text types from TTXIT for object KNA1 in current login language.

ZLSD_RPT10243_F01 – This include contains all class implementations (lcl_main), screen 100 modules, and global screen object declarations (go_container, go_splitter, go_top_cont, go_alv_cont, go_header_doc, go_grid, go_alv_obj, gs_layout).

START-OF-SELECTION
Instantiates lcl_main and calls its run() method to fetch and populate the global output table. Then calls display() which triggers CALL SCREEN 100 to render the ALV grid.

Class: lcl_main
Methods:

RUN – Main execution method. Fetches customer text data and populates gt_output.

Converts single PARAMETERs (p_ktokd, p_kukla, p_sortl, p_brsch) to range tables for SELECT filter.
Joins KNA1, KNVV, STXH and TTXIT to get all customer text headers matching selection screen criteria. Restricts to Z text types only.
Calls FM READ_TEXT for each customer and text type to retrieve actual text lines from TLINE.
Builds one output row per non-empty TDLINE. Customer and header fields (KUNNR, NAME1, TDID, TDTEXT) are populated only on the first line of each text block.
Returns without output and shows information popup if no data is found.


BUILD_FCAT – Builds the ALV field catalog. Defines six output columns: KUNNR (hotspot-enabled and key), NAME1, TDID, TDTEXT, SPRAS, and TDLINE. Column labels come from text symbols; output lengths are fixed per column.
DISPLAY – Calls CALL SCREEN 100 to render the ALV output screen.
HANDLE_HOTSPOT_CLICK – Fires when the user clicks a KUNNR cell. Reads the customer number from the clicked row and launches transaction XD02 via BDC, navigating automatically to the Texts screen (Extras → Texts) for that customer.
DOWNLOAD_DATA – Opens a Save File dialog (GUI_FILE_SAVE_DIALOG) with a default filename built from text symbols and current year. If the user confirms a path, calls GUI_DOWNLOAD to write gt_output as an ASCII tab-separated file with column headers. Displays a success or error message based on the return code.


Screen 100 Modules

STATUS_0100 (OUTPUT) – Sets PF-status and title bar. On first call: creates main custom container linked to screen control MAIN_CONTAINER. Creates easy splitter container (15% top / 85% bottom). Creates cl_dd_document in top container displaying selection criteria (Sales Org, Account Group, Customer Class, Industry, Text Type) as header. Creates ALV grid in bottom container, registers hotspot event handler, displays gt_output via set_table_for_first_display, and activates the interactive toolbar.
USER_COMMAND_0100 (INPUT) – Handles DOWNLOAD function code by calling go_alv_obj->download_data(). Handles BACK, EXIT, and CANCEL function codes by leaving program.


